1
00:00:04,776 --> 00:00:07,078
I wanted a job where I could make things.

2
00:00:09,180 --> 00:00:10,315
Like my dad.

3
00:00:11,449 --> 00:00:13,284
The pain the victim felt,

4
00:00:13,351 --> 00:00:15,286
and the pain the perpetrator feels…

5
00:00:15,353 --> 00:00:16,688
Now, they're equal.

6
00:00:17,388 --> 00:00:18,723
They're even.

7
00:00:22,093 --> 00:00:23,194
Nice and even.

8
00:00:41,880 --> 00:00:46,718
MINORU - CALL ME
TSUDA'S NOTEBOOK IS MISSING

9
00:00:56,995 --> 00:00:59,430
Excuse me, please don't look.

10
00:01:01,699 --> 00:01:02,867
Hello, sir.

11
00:01:07,038 --> 00:01:08,573
Mr. Tagusari, where did you go?

12
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:09,807
Who is the body?

13
00:01:09,874 --> 00:01:11,376
Takamichi Uno.

14
00:01:14,846 --> 00:01:18,216
Uno recently submitted
his resignation letter.

15
00:01:21,286 --> 00:01:23,121
So he did this to be with his wife.

16
00:01:23,188 --> 00:01:25,423
It's too early to jump to conclusions.

17
00:01:25,490 --> 00:01:29,427
Uno was caught on a surveillance camera
near Ayaka Nishiura's apartment.

18
00:01:30,161 --> 00:01:32,297
<i>There is no doubt that Uno killed her.</i>

19
00:01:32,363 --> 00:01:33,798
-What?
-Really?

20
00:01:33,865 --> 00:01:36,034
After finishing his revenge, Uno…

21
00:01:37,035 --> 00:01:38,636
Hello.

22
00:01:38,703 --> 00:01:40,305
-Hello.
-Hey.

23
00:01:44,475 --> 00:01:46,311
A fatal fall?

24
00:01:46,377 --> 00:01:47,278
Yes.

25
00:01:47,345 --> 00:01:49,314
Takamichi Uno, 50 years old, male.

26
00:01:49,380 --> 00:01:51,683
We got a report of him
falling around 6:00 p.m.

27
00:01:51,749 --> 00:01:54,085
We secured the scene and…

28
00:01:54,152 --> 00:01:55,753
It's a suicide.

29
00:01:55,820 --> 00:01:57,722
This one has no foul play.

30
00:02:07,999 --> 00:02:10,568
-I'm taking a look at the roof.
-Okay.

31
00:02:29,821 --> 00:02:31,756
Oh, Dr. Kiritani.

32
00:02:31,823 --> 00:02:33,925
Please handle the autopsy procedures.

33
00:02:34,759 --> 00:02:35,860
Yes.

34
00:02:38,529 --> 00:02:40,365
Don't add extra work for us.

35
00:02:42,667 --> 00:02:44,435
However you look at it, it’s suicide.

36
00:02:46,304 --> 00:02:48,706
I'm just doing my job.

37
00:02:48,773 --> 00:02:51,242
Uno's revenge is over. That's why he…

38
00:02:51,309 --> 00:02:52,210
I told you before.

39
00:02:52,844 --> 00:02:54,679
I'm only interested in the truth.

40
00:02:54,746 --> 00:02:58,216
-Uno jumped from the building!
-You want it to be suicide that badly?

41
00:02:58,283 --> 00:03:00,551
-That is the truth.
-It's not.

42
00:03:00,618 --> 00:03:01,953
Minoru.

43
00:03:02,887 --> 00:03:04,255
This isn't suicide.

44
00:03:05,256 --> 00:03:06,257
It's murder.

45
00:03:14,799 --> 00:03:17,335
All of this began three years ago.

46
00:03:17,402 --> 00:03:20,104
<i>Ms. Ayaka Nishiura was driving a car,</i>

47
00:03:20,171 --> 00:03:23,041
when she struck Yoko Uno,
who had jumped out into the road,

48
00:03:23,107 --> 00:03:24,709
and killed her.

49
00:03:25,343 --> 00:03:26,544
And the other day,

50
00:03:26,611 --> 00:03:31,082
<i>Ms. Nishiura</i>
<i>was murdered inside a moving car</i>

51
00:03:31,149 --> 00:03:32,684
<i>by carbon monoxide poisoning.</i>

52
00:03:32,750 --> 00:03:35,286
The suspect is Yoko's husband,

53
00:03:35,353 --> 00:03:37,255
Takamichi Uno.

54
00:03:37,322 --> 00:03:41,959
CCTV footage confirmed that the man
who tampered with Ms. Nishiura's car

55
00:03:42,026 --> 00:03:43,061
was Uno.

56
00:03:43,895 --> 00:03:47,598
We believe he held a grudge over losing
his wife, and did it for revenge.

57
00:03:48,266 --> 00:03:51,636
However, yesterday around 6:00 p.m.,

58
00:03:51,703 --> 00:03:53,938
<i>Takamichi Uno fell from a building.</i>

59
00:03:54,505 --> 00:03:56,374
<i>He was found dead.</i>

60
00:03:56,441 --> 00:03:57,975
Examiner Tagusari!

61
00:03:59,544 --> 00:04:01,279
Normally, in the case of a jump,

62
00:04:01,846 --> 00:04:04,449
the body lands
directly beneath the building.

63
00:04:04,515 --> 00:04:07,185
On the other hand, if a person is pushed,

64
00:04:07,251 --> 00:04:09,454
they fall in a parabolic arc,

65
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:13,324
so the landing point tends to be
a certain distance away from the building.

66
00:04:13,391 --> 00:04:16,594
The body was found
directly beneath the building, right?

67
00:04:16,661 --> 00:04:20,098
Takamichi Uno
struck something before landing.

68
00:04:20,665 --> 00:04:22,066
He struck something?

69
00:04:22,133 --> 00:04:24,035
<i>There were abrasions on his head,</i>

70
00:04:24,102 --> 00:04:27,839
<i>which matched the bloodstains found</i>
<i>on the wall of the adjacent building.</i>

71
00:04:28,506 --> 00:04:31,042
It is likely that Uno hit
the neighboring building,

72
00:04:31,609 --> 00:04:34,312
then landed directly underneath this one.

73
00:04:34,379 --> 00:04:35,813
Based on the above,

74
00:04:37,815 --> 00:04:41,252
it is highly likely
that this fatal fall was a homicide.

75
00:04:41,886 --> 00:04:45,123
We have to find witnesses,
trace his steps after quitting his job,

76
00:04:45,189 --> 00:04:48,126
and recover the data
from his damaged smartphone. Hurry!

77
00:04:48,659 --> 00:04:49,660
Yes, sir!

78
00:04:50,461 --> 00:04:51,529
What is it?

79
00:04:52,230 --> 00:04:55,333
May I check the alibi of Takumi Agatsuma?

80
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:57,201
<i>Ayaka Nishiura's fiancé?</i>

81
00:04:57,268 --> 00:04:59,137
Agatsuma has more than enough motive.

82
00:04:59,203 --> 00:05:00,338
It's pointless.

83
00:05:01,339 --> 00:05:04,175
It hasn't been made public
that Uno killed Nishiura.

84
00:05:04,242 --> 00:05:07,578
But, if we consider people
who may have a grudge against Uno,

85
00:05:07,645 --> 00:05:09,580
I think he is the most likely candidate.

86
00:05:09,647 --> 00:05:11,616
True, we can't ignore Agatsuma.

87
00:05:12,984 --> 00:05:14,786
However, drop your preconceptions.

88
00:05:14,852 --> 00:05:17,555
If you label someone a suspect,
that's all you'll see.

89
00:05:18,689 --> 00:05:19,824
Understood.

90
00:05:22,126 --> 00:05:23,795
Anyone checked the cameras?

91
00:05:23,861 --> 00:05:24,695
Yes!

92
00:05:25,263 --> 00:05:27,432
But we haven't found a suspect yet.

93
00:05:29,834 --> 00:05:30,701
<i>Mr. Agatsuma,</i>

94
00:05:31,335 --> 00:05:34,172
where were you yesterday around 6:00 p.m.?

95
00:05:35,540 --> 00:05:36,941
Yesterday, I went with…

96
00:05:37,642 --> 00:05:40,745
my parents to the real estate agency
to cancel the lease on my place,

97
00:05:40,812 --> 00:05:42,346
then went home.

98
00:05:42,413 --> 00:05:43,714
After that, were you alone?

99
00:05:44,715 --> 00:05:46,083
Yes.

100
00:05:46,150 --> 00:05:47,518
That's enough.

101
00:05:50,321 --> 00:05:51,355
Excuse me.

102
00:05:51,856 --> 00:05:53,124
Mr. Tagusari.

103
00:05:58,496 --> 00:06:01,833
WELFARE OFFICE CONSULTATIONS
COME TALK TO ME ANYTIME!

104
00:06:01,899 --> 00:06:03,668
KANAGAWA POLICE

105
00:06:08,072 --> 00:06:10,041
RECOVERED DATA FROM APPS
TELESEEK

106
00:06:10,107 --> 00:06:11,776
Mr. Tagusari!

107
00:06:12,810 --> 00:06:15,379
Ms. Kudo is here to see you.

108
00:06:19,817 --> 00:06:21,085
It's about Detective Tagusari.

109
00:06:21,853 --> 00:06:24,121
Don't you think
he has been acting weird lately?

110
00:06:24,188 --> 00:06:25,423
Lately?

111
00:06:25,490 --> 00:06:29,460
He is often unreachable
and abruptly cuts investigations short.

112
00:06:30,528 --> 00:06:34,232
I know he thinks of things as a hassle,
but this feels different.

113
00:06:34,932 --> 00:06:36,734
When did it start bothering you?

114
00:06:37,301 --> 00:06:39,403
After he went to the city hall, I think.

115
00:06:39,470 --> 00:06:40,805
The city hall?

116
00:06:40,872 --> 00:06:44,041
The welfare consultant there
doesn't sit right with me.

117
00:06:45,743 --> 00:06:49,747
Now, three of her consultees
have become murder suspects.

118
00:06:50,982 --> 00:06:52,617
Takumi Agatsuma,

119
00:06:53,484 --> 00:06:56,387
Takamichi Uno, and Atsuko Narita.

120
00:06:57,388 --> 00:06:58,489
Narita?

121
00:06:58,556 --> 00:07:01,726
The mother from the case
of the AI grading error.

122
00:07:03,327 --> 00:07:05,530
<i>The one I'm stuck on is the mother.</i>

123
00:07:06,030 --> 00:07:09,133
I saw a TeleSeek notification
on her phone.

124
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:11,836
<i>That app that doesn't store</i>
<i>message history?</i>

125
00:07:12,637 --> 00:07:16,440
Could it be that the consultant urged
the three of them to commit murder?

126
00:07:17,375 --> 00:07:18,976
What is her name?

127
00:07:19,544 --> 00:07:20,811
It's Sayoko Hatano.

128
00:07:20,878 --> 00:07:22,013
WELFARE CONSULTANT

129
00:07:26,817 --> 00:07:29,420
<i>Only the bereaved</i>
<i>who have lost their loved ones…</i>

130
00:07:29,487 --> 00:07:30,488
<i>Why?</i>

131
00:07:31,088 --> 00:07:33,791
<i>Why must they be the ones</i>
<i>to continue suffering?</i>

132
00:07:40,498 --> 00:07:44,535
KANAGAWA POLICE
MAKOTO TAGUSARI

133
00:07:51,609 --> 00:07:53,044
-Ms. Hatano.
-Yes?

134
00:07:53,110 --> 00:07:55,346
A Mr. Tagusari is here for you.

135
00:07:56,013 --> 00:07:57,281
Okay.

136
00:08:14,699 --> 00:08:16,934
So you are Minoru, his younger brother?

137
00:08:17,969 --> 00:08:21,339
I heard from Makoto
that you work as a forensics examiner.

138
00:08:22,173 --> 00:08:24,675
You're so talented for your age.

139
00:08:26,577 --> 00:08:28,479
What did you talk to him about?

140
00:08:29,347 --> 00:08:30,615
Are you curious?

141
00:08:31,248 --> 00:08:32,416
Yes, I am.

142
00:08:33,217 --> 00:08:37,388
You majored in criminal psychology.
What could he be talking about with you?

143
00:08:40,157 --> 00:08:42,827
I'm sorry,
I inquired with your university.

144
00:08:45,496 --> 00:08:47,064
Could you tell me?

145
00:08:48,132 --> 00:08:49,667
I can't disclose my consultation--

146
00:08:49,734 --> 00:08:51,135
This is also a consultation.

147
00:08:52,536 --> 00:08:54,772
I am consulting about my brother.

148
00:08:59,877 --> 00:09:04,315
I listened to what was at his core.

149
00:09:06,851 --> 00:09:10,788
I'm sure those are things
he could never tell anyone, not even you.

150
00:09:11,389 --> 00:09:13,457
What's at his core.

151
00:09:17,995 --> 00:09:18,963
But…

152
00:09:19,864 --> 00:09:21,532
you have them too, don't you?

153
00:09:22,933 --> 00:09:25,403
Things you can't tell your older brother?

154
00:09:28,105 --> 00:09:30,207
I don't. Not really.

155
00:09:30,274 --> 00:09:33,244
If you want my counsel, you must not lie.

156
00:09:36,814 --> 00:09:38,249
COME TALK TO ME ANYTIME!

157
00:09:38,315 --> 00:09:41,085
Hatano might have been
inciting the murders.

158
00:09:41,686 --> 00:09:43,688
Even if she led them to commit crimes,

159
00:09:43,754 --> 00:09:45,923
it would be difficult
to build a legal case.

160
00:09:46,424 --> 00:09:48,693
I'll probe into her background
with First Division.

161
00:09:48,759 --> 00:09:49,860
Please do.

162
00:09:52,430 --> 00:09:54,365
Oh, where is Tagusari?

163
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:58,202
He's not feeling well.

164
00:10:04,108 --> 00:10:08,112
Since that day,
Makoto has always protected you, right?

165
00:10:10,581 --> 00:10:12,583
You were still so young.

166
00:10:12,650 --> 00:10:15,553
It's no wonder
you shut yourself away, Minoru.

167
00:10:17,188 --> 00:10:19,356
But, you knew…

168
00:10:20,224 --> 00:10:21,592
didn't you?

169
00:10:24,161 --> 00:10:27,898
What your brother, who was only seven,
had been carrying since that day.

170
00:10:35,172 --> 00:10:36,841
Aside from the incident,

171
00:10:37,341 --> 00:10:42,379
Makoto had to fill the void
left by your deceased parents.

172
00:10:44,715 --> 00:10:46,117
His daily life,

173
00:10:46,183 --> 00:10:49,019
his studies and future.

174
00:10:51,288 --> 00:10:56,393
He prioritized you
over himself, didn't he, Minoru?

175
00:11:00,731 --> 00:11:05,136
And you began to feel guilty about that.

176
00:11:08,072 --> 00:11:12,309
Thinking that you couldn't
do anything for your brother.

177
00:11:15,312 --> 00:11:16,447
It's almost like

178
00:11:17,648 --> 00:11:19,383
you saw my whole life story.

179
00:11:20,417 --> 00:11:21,385
But…

180
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:25,156
there is something you can do.

181
00:11:27,024 --> 00:11:29,527
There are things that only you can do.

182
00:11:31,095 --> 00:11:33,430
<i>However, I'll be the one to do it.</i>

183
00:11:34,465 --> 00:11:36,300
I will carry him at the end.

184
00:11:39,703 --> 00:11:41,038
This time,

185
00:11:42,306 --> 00:11:47,278
won't you tell me
what's at your core, Minoru?

186
00:11:58,489 --> 00:11:59,423
You should take it.

187
00:11:59,924 --> 00:12:02,493
All right. Excuse me.

188
00:12:04,061 --> 00:12:05,563
Oh, they hung up.

189
00:12:08,432 --> 00:12:10,801
It's an unknown number.

190
00:12:11,869 --> 00:12:13,037
A spam call?

191
00:12:13,537 --> 00:12:15,105
-I see.
-Right.

192
00:12:15,172 --> 00:12:17,408
There are a lot of scams lately,
so be careful.

193
00:12:19,043 --> 00:12:20,211
Oh, sorry.

194
00:12:20,744 --> 00:12:22,413
I'll go get a cloth.

195
00:12:32,356 --> 00:12:33,691
ONE MISSED CALL

196
00:12:33,757 --> 00:12:36,427
TELESEEK

197
00:12:46,203 --> 00:12:47,137
Makoto?

198
00:12:52,176 --> 00:12:53,811
What are you doing here?

199
00:12:54,879 --> 00:12:56,347
What about you?

200
00:13:00,084 --> 00:13:01,418
We need to talk.

201
00:13:10,361 --> 00:13:13,464
I found the TeleSeek app
on Sayoko Hatano's phone too.

202
00:13:15,633 --> 00:13:18,235
They must be sending messages
that could be evidence.

203
00:13:19,203 --> 00:13:23,340
Which means, no matter how much we dig,
we won't find anything.

204
00:13:25,309 --> 00:13:27,177
She's a troublesome opponent.

205
00:13:33,450 --> 00:13:34,418
Makoto!

206
00:13:34,485 --> 00:13:36,520
Who are the real troublesome ones?

207
00:13:37,354 --> 00:13:39,623
The perpetrators
who don't get judged, right?

208
00:13:41,892 --> 00:13:44,561
Hold on! The Igarashi-gumi
disposed of the notebook.

209
00:13:44,628 --> 00:13:46,230
I am very sorry!

210
00:13:50,868 --> 00:13:52,036
Sakuraba.

211
00:13:52,102 --> 00:13:54,071
Did anything come up besides the drugs?

212
00:13:55,372 --> 00:13:56,640
Are you kidding me?

213
00:13:57,207 --> 00:13:58,175
What?

214
00:13:58,242 --> 00:14:00,210
You gave me false info.

215
00:14:01,378 --> 00:14:02,413
This.

216
00:14:06,116 --> 00:14:08,218
HARUKO ASHIKAGA
THE IGARASHI-GUMI'S CLEANERS

217
00:14:08,285 --> 00:14:09,420
Their cleaners?

218
00:14:09,486 --> 00:14:11,689
We might find Tsuda's notebook there.

219
00:14:22,533 --> 00:14:24,134
We're closed for the day.

220
00:14:24,201 --> 00:14:25,669
Come back tomorrow.

221
00:14:26,770 --> 00:14:28,839
I'm sorry, but I'm busy tomorrow.

222
00:14:35,479 --> 00:14:36,880
I'm glad.

223
00:14:36,947 --> 00:14:38,482
Do you remember me?

224
00:14:39,950 --> 00:14:41,251
What do you want?

225
00:14:42,686 --> 00:14:45,456
Don't be so on guard.

226
00:14:46,023 --> 00:14:47,958
You're not here to see the wares, right?

227
00:14:49,893 --> 00:14:51,795
Why did you come back here?

228
00:14:52,896 --> 00:14:54,932
Just by chance, that's all.

229
00:14:56,233 --> 00:14:57,067
Back then,

230
00:14:58,736 --> 00:15:00,004
was it "by chance," too?

231
00:15:00,571 --> 00:15:01,538
What?

232
00:15:02,373 --> 00:15:04,008
The day of the murders.

233
00:15:04,842 --> 00:15:07,144
Why were you in front
of the Tagusaris's home?

234
00:15:08,645 --> 00:15:10,247
When are you talking about?

235
00:15:11,181 --> 00:15:13,083
1995.

236
00:15:13,150 --> 00:15:14,551
<i>April 26.</i>

237
00:15:15,652 --> 00:15:18,322
<i>Around 10:54 p.m.</i>

238
00:15:21,592 --> 00:15:22,760
Why were you there?

239
00:15:25,229 --> 00:15:26,730
I told you already.

240
00:15:26,797 --> 00:15:29,433
I was passing by on my way home
from my part-time job.

241
00:15:31,168 --> 00:15:34,338
It has been 30 years.
Stop interrogating me.

242
00:15:34,405 --> 00:15:36,807
Then stop helping those brothers.

243
00:15:37,608 --> 00:15:40,444
You know what those guys
are doing, don't you?

244
00:15:43,113 --> 00:15:44,815
The statute has expired.

245
00:15:46,216 --> 00:15:48,685
That case is over now.

246
00:15:55,292 --> 00:15:57,227
Stop selling fakes.

247
00:16:00,097 --> 00:16:01,532
Is Mr. Sasaoka…

248
00:16:02,833 --> 00:16:04,368
doing well?

249
00:16:09,406 --> 00:16:13,243
I heard your partner back then
was forced to quit being a detective.

250
00:16:13,310 --> 00:16:14,344
INSPECTOR DISCHARGED

251
00:16:14,411 --> 00:16:16,046
<i>So this is where you were.</i>

252
00:16:18,882 --> 00:16:21,819
Ex-Detective Sasaoka from First Division.

253
00:16:22,319 --> 00:16:26,757
I heard you used to be quite close
with the Igarashi-gumi.

254
00:16:35,065 --> 00:16:39,369
INSPECTOR DISCHARGED FOR LEAKING
CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION

255
00:16:46,210 --> 00:16:47,711
Hey, you guys.

256
00:16:47,778 --> 00:16:50,447
I heard you guys
can dispose of anything here.

257
00:16:50,514 --> 00:16:52,983
Do you really accept everything?

258
00:16:53,050 --> 00:16:56,954
Let's say we have something
we don't want anyone to see.

259
00:16:58,956 --> 00:17:02,126
We only work with companies
we have a contract with.

260
00:17:02,192 --> 00:17:03,927
Do you mean the Igarashi-gumi?

261
00:17:05,129 --> 00:17:08,732
This place is the Igarashi-gumi's
dumping ground, right?

262
00:17:10,434 --> 00:17:12,736
Show me the things
you've received recently.

263
00:17:12,803 --> 00:17:16,206
What are you talking about?
No way we have anything like that.

264
00:17:16,273 --> 00:17:17,274
This.

265
00:17:17,341 --> 00:17:19,676
You want me to show it
to the Igarashi-gumi?

266
00:17:23,180 --> 00:17:26,783
You only pretend to dispose of them,
but you've actually been reselling them.

267
00:17:27,584 --> 00:17:29,786
If the Igarashi-gumi finds out about this…

268
00:17:49,273 --> 00:17:51,408
Can you really restore
something like that?

269
00:17:51,909 --> 00:17:53,510
We have no choice but to try.

270
00:17:54,311 --> 00:17:56,680
Because Tsuda's notebook is inside this.

271
00:17:58,015 --> 00:17:59,883
You used to like puzzles.

272
00:18:05,689 --> 00:18:08,225
It's not like I did puzzles
because I liked them.

273
00:18:11,762 --> 00:18:13,263
After the incident,

274
00:18:14,932 --> 00:18:16,567
I just didn't want to go outside.

275
00:18:21,438 --> 00:18:25,209
Back then, everywhere I went,
people stared at me,

276
00:18:26,944 --> 00:18:28,845
they all looked like enemies to me.

277
00:18:31,882 --> 00:18:35,752
Friends, adults,
people I met for the first time…

278
00:18:38,188 --> 00:18:41,992
Well, that hasn't changed even now, but…

279
00:18:46,330 --> 00:18:49,199
At this point,
I'm even afraid of making allies.

280
00:18:59,610 --> 00:19:00,877
I know.

281
00:19:08,518 --> 00:19:10,487
Sayoko Hatano is the enemy, you know.

282
00:19:21,131 --> 00:19:23,166
She's just pretending to be our ally.

283
00:19:53,930 --> 00:19:55,899
Put the white paper in a separate pile.

284
00:20:11,848 --> 00:20:15,385
Go steal the evidence from those brothers.

285
00:20:28,298 --> 00:20:30,000
Why the sudden visit?

286
00:20:32,402 --> 00:20:33,904
-Oh…
-Do you want…

287
00:20:34,438 --> 00:20:35,872
Do you want something to drink?

288
00:20:37,874 --> 00:20:41,345
I can't betray those boys after all.

289
00:20:46,016 --> 00:20:48,318
I've known them since they were kids.

290
00:20:49,152 --> 00:20:50,320
I can't…

291
00:20:51,621 --> 00:20:53,056
What about us?

292
00:20:54,758 --> 00:20:57,761
We've known you
since before they were even born, right?

293
00:20:59,296 --> 00:21:01,331
That's true, but…

294
00:21:04,701 --> 00:21:07,204
Do you not care what happens to us?

295
00:21:09,039 --> 00:21:10,240
No…

296
00:21:10,307 --> 00:21:11,441
Mogi!

297
00:21:23,086 --> 00:21:25,822
Oh, right!

298
00:21:25,889 --> 00:21:27,057
The other day,

299
00:21:27,124 --> 00:21:29,893
I took some test shots with my new camera!

300
00:21:31,895 --> 00:21:35,031
Karu, had such
a wonderful expression on her face.

301
00:21:36,767 --> 00:21:38,101
Take it home with you.

302
00:21:44,474 --> 00:21:45,876
Mogi.

303
00:21:49,246 --> 00:21:53,850
It's for the sake of everyone.
So we can all be happy.

304
00:22:20,377 --> 00:22:21,545
Minoru!

305
00:22:22,446 --> 00:22:24,948
Don't talk about cases
in a place like this.

306
00:22:25,015 --> 00:22:26,383
You're fine, Mogi.

307
00:22:39,696 --> 00:22:43,700
The consultant, Sayoko Hatano,
was in charge of three suspects.

308
00:22:44,568 --> 00:22:46,937
The first was Atsuko Narita.

309
00:22:47,437 --> 00:22:50,273
Her son, Kenshin, came forward
to take the blame for her.

310
00:22:50,340 --> 00:22:52,976
Atsuko herself has not confessed.

311
00:22:53,043 --> 00:22:56,012
Her presumed method
was a lethal combination of medications.

312
00:22:56,580 --> 00:22:58,648
We found a newspaper article
about the method.

313
00:22:58,715 --> 00:23:00,584
PRESCRIPTION ERROR LED
TO 63-YEAR-OLD WOMAN'S DEATH

314
00:23:00,650 --> 00:23:03,286
The second person was Takamichi Uno.

315
00:23:04,187 --> 00:23:06,356
It is believed he murdered

316
00:23:06,423 --> 00:23:10,227
Ms. Ayaka Nishiura while she was driving,
using carbon monoxide poisoning.

317
00:23:10,293 --> 00:23:14,164
This is a mystery novel
that utilizes a similar trick.

318
00:23:14,231 --> 00:23:17,467
And the third person is Takumi Agatsuma.

319
00:23:17,534 --> 00:23:20,637
It's possible she led him
to pushing Uno to his death.

320
00:23:20,704 --> 00:23:22,839
According to
a Welfare Department colleague,

321
00:23:23,406 --> 00:23:26,309
Hatano would recommend books
and materials to her consultees.

322
00:23:26,810 --> 00:23:28,578
It's highly probable she used those

323
00:23:28,645 --> 00:23:31,348
to suggest methods of murder,
prompting them to seek revenge.

324
00:23:31,414 --> 00:23:34,751
However, because Uno used
an app with high encryption,

325
00:23:34,818 --> 00:23:37,254
no evidence could be recovered
from his smartphone.

326
00:23:37,821 --> 00:23:40,323
The TeleSeek app was also present
on Hatano's phone,

327
00:23:40,390 --> 00:23:42,259
but that isn't enough to build a case.

328
00:23:42,859 --> 00:23:45,161
We must find definitive evidence
of the murder

329
00:23:45,228 --> 00:23:48,431
and force a link to Hatano's involvement.

330
00:23:58,542 --> 00:24:00,043
<i>Why go that far?</i>

331
00:24:00,577 --> 00:24:03,213
<i>Well, they're a bit similar</i>
<i>to my own family.</i>

332
00:24:04,648 --> 00:24:07,083
My dad was always busy,

333
00:24:07,784 --> 00:24:10,086
so we barely spent any time together.

334
00:24:10,720 --> 00:24:12,789
It was mostly just my mother and me.

335
00:24:13,557 --> 00:24:16,092
I caused her
quite a lot of trouble back then,

336
00:24:17,027 --> 00:24:20,397
so now I want to put her mind at ease.

337
00:24:22,732 --> 00:24:26,436
That's why I think
Narita's son will understand too.

338
00:24:27,537 --> 00:24:32,008
That it's his turn now
to save his mother, who made a wrong turn.

339
00:24:41,851 --> 00:24:43,653
Reporting to Ayaka?

340
00:24:46,723 --> 00:24:48,892
Since it's all over,
won't you talk to me now?

341
00:24:49,392 --> 00:24:51,094
What are you talking about?

342
00:25:04,407 --> 00:25:06,543
Don't you think it's strange?

343
00:25:08,545 --> 00:25:10,580
Why doesn't everyone take revenge?

344
00:25:13,750 --> 00:25:17,587
"If anything ever happened to my child,
I would never forgive them."

345
00:25:18,989 --> 00:25:21,157
You hear people say that all the time,

346
00:25:22,058 --> 00:25:23,360
but barely anyone acts on it.

347
00:25:26,630 --> 00:25:29,766
They use their remaining family
as an excuse

348
00:25:29,833 --> 00:25:31,901
to force a lid on their own feelings.

349
00:25:35,271 --> 00:25:37,907
And Sayoko Hatano pried open that lid

350
00:25:39,275 --> 00:25:41,711
which you had fought
so hard to keep closed.

351
00:25:46,116 --> 00:25:48,385
Though she never experienced
any pain herself.

352
00:25:52,022 --> 00:25:53,556
Is Sayoko Hatano…

353
00:25:55,091 --> 00:25:57,394
truly on your side?

354
00:26:05,068 --> 00:26:06,603
Excuse me.

355
00:26:06,670 --> 00:26:08,004
Mr. Agatsuma.

356
00:26:08,505 --> 00:26:09,572
Blue.

357
00:26:10,607 --> 00:26:11,975
Transparent.

358
00:26:12,709 --> 00:26:14,010
Purple.

359
00:26:14,077 --> 00:26:14,911
White.

360
00:26:26,589 --> 00:26:27,524
The roof?

361
00:26:30,226 --> 00:26:31,695
There they are.

362
00:26:31,761 --> 00:26:33,997
What are you doing?

363
00:26:34,064 --> 00:26:35,799
Help us search for the power stones!

364
00:26:35,865 --> 00:26:38,101
Can you explain more clearly?

365
00:26:38,168 --> 00:26:41,071
Agatsuma wore a matching
bracelet with his girlfriend.

366
00:26:41,137 --> 00:26:44,074
After the murder, the arrangement
of the stones changed.

367
00:26:44,140 --> 00:26:45,141
Arrangement?

368
00:26:45,208 --> 00:26:46,309
After the murder,

369
00:26:46,376 --> 00:26:48,545
<i>a single white stone was missing.</i>

370
00:26:48,611 --> 00:26:50,180
How did you even notice that?

371
00:26:50,246 --> 00:26:54,851
If the bracelet snapped
when he pushed Uno off the building here…

372
00:26:54,918 --> 00:26:57,454
The stones he missed might still be here.

373
00:26:57,520 --> 00:26:59,723
So, what if we find those stones?

374
00:27:00,590 --> 00:27:02,992
It means Agatsuma was definitely here.

375
00:27:07,230 --> 00:27:08,598
Come to think of it,

376
00:27:09,766 --> 00:27:13,436
Fumi comes to the restaurant often these…

377
00:27:13,503 --> 00:27:14,571
This is…

378
00:27:15,138 --> 00:27:16,206
the back side.

379
00:27:17,741 --> 00:27:18,408
There.

380
00:27:18,908 --> 00:27:19,843
Oh, right.

381
00:27:20,410 --> 00:27:21,277
Amazing.

382
00:27:21,778 --> 00:27:24,948
Since I was a kid, I often
got absorbed in things like this.

383
00:27:25,014 --> 00:27:26,282
Same with cooking, right?

384
00:27:26,850 --> 00:27:30,120
Well, once I get started,
I just can't stop.

385
00:27:32,522 --> 00:27:34,290
Shall we eat soon?

386
00:27:35,325 --> 00:27:36,359
What about Makoto?

387
00:27:36,426 --> 00:27:38,094
I don't know when he'll be back.

388
00:27:41,030 --> 00:27:42,932
I'll make something.

389
00:27:42,999 --> 00:27:44,067
Really?

390
00:27:44,801 --> 00:27:47,270
We have nothing here,
I'll run to the supermarket.

391
00:27:47,337 --> 00:27:48,171
What?

392
00:27:48,238 --> 00:27:49,639
Keep working on that.

393
00:28:09,425 --> 00:28:12,829
<i>Go steal the evidence from those brothers.</i>

394
00:28:21,404 --> 00:28:24,507
I wonder if he picked up all the stones…

395
00:28:25,675 --> 00:28:27,944
Or maybe it snapped
somewhere else entirely,

396
00:28:28,011 --> 00:28:29,879
completely unrelated to the murder.

397
00:28:30,580 --> 00:28:32,115
Shall we call it a day soon?

398
00:28:32,182 --> 00:28:34,083
We've hit a complete dead end.

399
00:28:45,228 --> 00:28:46,396
-Kudo.
-Yes?

400
00:28:46,462 --> 00:28:47,330
I need a handsaw.

401
00:28:47,397 --> 00:28:48,498
What?

402
00:28:49,065 --> 00:28:50,166
What for?

403
00:28:50,233 --> 00:28:53,036
Ishizaka, go up to the rooftop
run water down the pipe.

404
00:28:53,102 --> 00:28:54,170
-What?
-Hurry up.

405
00:28:54,237 --> 00:28:55,171
-What?
-Move it!

406
00:28:55,238 --> 00:28:56,072
Okay.

407
00:29:03,780 --> 00:29:04,781
That day,

408
00:29:05,782 --> 00:29:08,117
I went to the rooftop,
like the counselor told me to.

409
00:29:08,685 --> 00:29:11,654
How did you get Uno
to go up to the rooftop?

410
00:29:11,721 --> 00:29:14,390
She called him out for me.

411
00:29:16,392 --> 00:29:17,493
And after that?

412
00:29:27,503 --> 00:29:28,838
Are we bringing Hatano in?

413
00:29:28,905 --> 00:29:30,306
No, it's impossible.

414
00:29:30,940 --> 00:29:33,243
We have no evidence
she ordered the murder,

415
00:29:33,309 --> 00:29:35,612
nor do we have proof
that she called Uno out.

416
00:29:37,046 --> 00:29:39,115
If only we had that, we could arrest her.

417
00:29:39,182 --> 00:29:42,952
But Hatano has been meticulous
about erasing all traces.

418
00:29:47,657 --> 00:29:48,625
Mrs. Narita.

419
00:29:51,995 --> 00:29:53,730
What is the matter?

420
00:29:55,265 --> 00:29:57,000
I spoke with my son.

421
00:29:58,668 --> 00:30:01,037
I will tell you the truth.

422
00:30:02,272 --> 00:30:05,942
In Mr. Ichijo's murder,
there were a few unclear points.

423
00:30:06,542 --> 00:30:09,579
How did you find out about
the cover-up of the grading errors?

424
00:30:10,246 --> 00:30:11,814
Through a tablet.

425
00:30:11,881 --> 00:30:13,716
-Once in the morning.
<i>-Mr. Ichijo…</i>

426
00:30:14,417 --> 00:30:17,587
<i>He frequented the pharmacy where I worked.</i>

427
00:30:17,654 --> 00:30:19,022
Here you go.

428
00:30:19,622 --> 00:30:21,925
<i>One day, when he went</i>
<i>to get his prescription,</i>

429
00:30:21,991 --> 00:30:23,326
<i>he forgot his tablet.</i>

430
00:30:23,826 --> 00:30:26,696
<i>I immediately tried to run after him, but…</i>

431
00:30:28,765 --> 00:30:30,266
MASAOMI OKAMURA
ABOUT THE GRADING ERROR

432
00:30:30,333 --> 00:30:31,167
What?

433
00:30:31,801 --> 00:30:33,202
ABOUT THE GRADING ERROR

434
00:30:33,269 --> 00:30:34,737
It's just a prank email.

435
00:30:34,804 --> 00:30:37,707
But the email clearly mentions an error.

436
00:30:38,341 --> 00:30:42,879
I won't tell a soul,
so could you please let my son pass?

437
00:30:45,014 --> 00:30:46,182
How much do you want?

438
00:30:47,250 --> 00:30:48,117
What?

439
00:30:48,184 --> 00:30:51,154
I bet your goal is money, right?

440
00:30:52,355 --> 00:30:53,222
Darling.

441
00:30:53,289 --> 00:30:54,157
You have a guest?

442
00:30:54,223 --> 00:30:57,660
-I'll be done soon.
<i>-He didn't even take me seriously.</i>

443
00:30:57,727 --> 00:31:00,096
But to go as far as murder…

444
00:31:02,098 --> 00:31:04,300
Surely there were other ways
to make it public?

445
00:31:05,969 --> 00:31:09,739
I went to the city hall,
and Ms. Hatano told me…

446
00:31:11,507 --> 00:31:13,743
"The university would never admit to it,

447
00:31:14,711 --> 00:31:17,513
and it would probably just be covered up.

448
00:31:19,382 --> 00:31:23,453
If things stayed like this, Kenshin
would be the only one left to suffer."

449
00:31:25,388 --> 00:31:26,689
I just couldn't

450
00:31:28,224 --> 00:31:29,926
bring myself to forgive them.

451
00:31:33,429 --> 00:31:35,498
Why couldn't you stop yourself?

452
00:31:39,669 --> 00:31:41,704
Now that you, his mother, have done this,

453
00:31:42,839 --> 00:31:44,507
it only makes it harder for him.

454
00:31:48,644 --> 00:31:51,581
ADVICE FROM MOM
DON'T PUSH YOURSELF TOO HARD!

455
00:31:54,550 --> 00:31:56,953
TO KENSHIN

456
00:32:00,890 --> 00:32:03,893
There's no doubt that Hatano also incited
Narita to commit murder.

457
00:32:03,960 --> 00:32:05,261
What about the evidence?

458
00:32:05,328 --> 00:32:08,564
Hatano merely laid out
facts and possibilities.

459
00:32:08,631 --> 00:32:11,768
And she only showed a newspaper article
for the murder method.

460
00:32:11,834 --> 00:32:13,936
That doesn't warrant an arrest.

461
00:32:14,604 --> 00:32:15,738
Then, Hatano…

462
00:32:17,240 --> 00:32:20,510
We might have
to take the loss on this one.

463
00:32:28,284 --> 00:32:29,752
Where are you going?

464
00:32:33,322 --> 00:32:35,091
Causing trouble for your partner again?

465
00:32:36,292 --> 00:32:38,394
-What did you come here for?
-For work.

466
00:32:39,262 --> 00:32:40,430
And also…

467
00:32:42,031 --> 00:32:45,435
Hatano incited others to kill,
without leaving traces of herself.

468
00:32:46,002 --> 00:32:48,438
However, while she used
an article for Narita

469
00:32:48,504 --> 00:32:50,606
and a mystery novel for Uno,

470
00:32:50,673 --> 00:32:53,976
we couldn't find any clear motif
regarding Agatsuma's homicide.

471
00:32:54,043 --> 00:32:56,646
True, Uno's death
was handled as a fatal fall.

472
00:32:57,747 --> 00:32:59,949
Maybe their plan went off the rails?

473
00:33:00,550 --> 00:33:03,052
Since Uno had submitted
a resignation letter,

474
00:33:03,119 --> 00:33:05,555
there was a possibility
he was attempting to flee.

475
00:33:06,055 --> 00:33:08,624
That's why Agatsuma needed to hurry.

476
00:33:08,691 --> 00:33:10,993
Which means Sayoko Hatano also…

477
00:33:13,529 --> 00:33:16,732
As for the rest, you'll understand
once you check this data.

478
00:33:17,366 --> 00:33:18,835
I'll go check it.

479
00:33:23,573 --> 00:33:25,675
Did you plan to become bait?

480
00:33:27,110 --> 00:33:28,344
Not really.

481
00:33:28,411 --> 00:33:30,613
Hatano is going to manipulate you again.

482
00:33:30,680 --> 00:33:32,448
Shut up. Like hell she will.

483
00:33:33,316 --> 00:33:35,585
If that's the case,
make sure you bring her down.

484
00:33:39,255 --> 00:33:41,057
I can't stand her.

485
00:33:53,202 --> 00:33:54,604
Wait here.

486
00:33:54,670 --> 00:33:55,605
What?

487
00:33:59,242 --> 00:34:01,944
I met your younger brother the other day.

488
00:34:04,180 --> 00:34:06,816
Please bring him with you next time.

489
00:34:08,918 --> 00:34:10,920
We won't meet again.

490
00:34:12,355 --> 00:34:15,291
I'm here today to arrest you.

491
00:34:16,993 --> 00:34:17,894
Arrest?

492
00:34:19,095 --> 00:34:20,429
You have consulted

493
00:34:21,597 --> 00:34:24,367
with various people in this office.

494
00:34:25,434 --> 00:34:26,536
Your consultees

495
00:34:27,570 --> 00:34:30,373
trusted you so deeply,
they spoke your name with respect.

496
00:34:32,575 --> 00:34:36,312
But, in those sessions,
you were carefully examining them.

497
00:34:37,613 --> 00:34:39,148
The depth of their wounds.

498
00:34:42,251 --> 00:34:43,686
Atsuko Narita,

499
00:34:44,353 --> 00:34:45,721
Takamichi Uno,

500
00:34:45,788 --> 00:34:47,523
and Takumi Agatsuma.

501
00:34:48,224 --> 00:34:51,027
You found clients who had someone
they wanted revenge on,

502
00:34:51,093 --> 00:34:52,995
and goaded them into committing murder.

503
00:34:56,199 --> 00:35:00,736
I was simply doing my job.

504
00:35:04,807 --> 00:35:06,108
Your job?

505
00:35:06,676 --> 00:35:08,678
I merely listened to their worries,

506
00:35:09,312 --> 00:35:13,549
and occasionally recommended books
or other material, for a change of pace.

507
00:35:15,251 --> 00:35:18,654
How is any of that a crime?

508
00:35:22,858 --> 00:35:23,993
True,

509
00:35:24,961 --> 00:35:27,363
if that's all, you wouldn't be
judged by the law.

510
00:35:28,464 --> 00:35:29,432
But,

511
00:35:31,901 --> 00:35:34,804
the final one, Takumi Agatsuma,
was different, wasn't he?

512
00:35:36,706 --> 00:35:39,275
Uno, the target of his revenge,
attempted to flee.

513
00:35:39,842 --> 00:35:42,878
He probably got cold feet
because the police were closing in.

514
00:35:44,013 --> 00:35:45,014
However,

515
00:35:45,581 --> 00:35:48,818
if Uno escaped,
Agatsuma's revenge would fail.

516
00:35:49,552 --> 00:35:53,155
You called Uno to that building,
pretending to give him runaway funds.

517
00:35:53,823 --> 00:35:55,625
Then you led Agatsuma there,

518
00:35:56,626 --> 00:35:58,828
setting things up
so that he would kill him.

519
00:36:01,597 --> 00:36:04,100
To trigger a cycle of revenge.

520
00:36:13,309 --> 00:36:14,744
You seem remarkably composed.

521
00:36:16,312 --> 00:36:18,381
If I look that way to you,

522
00:36:19,582 --> 00:36:21,417
perhaps I am.

523
00:36:25,288 --> 00:36:26,555
It's true that

524
00:36:27,056 --> 00:36:30,326
because you used TeleSeek,
there is no physical evidence.

525
00:36:31,060 --> 00:36:32,561
Even if Agatsuma testifies,

526
00:36:32,628 --> 00:36:35,298
if you deny it,
the truth remains out of reach.

527
00:36:38,968 --> 00:36:41,037
So, how are you arresting me?

528
00:36:41,103 --> 00:36:42,571
Don't misunderstand.

529
00:36:43,239 --> 00:36:45,141
The lack of evidence

530
00:36:46,609 --> 00:36:48,244
is only on your consultee's side.

531
00:36:50,212 --> 00:36:52,381
Uno's sudden escape was unexpected.

532
00:36:53,082 --> 00:36:56,419
That's why you had to rush
Agatsuma into the crime.

533
00:36:59,922 --> 00:37:02,825
You had no choice but to give
instructions from right here.

534
00:37:09,865 --> 00:37:11,167
This is

535
00:37:12,201 --> 00:37:16,472
security footage from the city hall,
one hour before Uno was murdered.

536
00:37:26,015 --> 00:37:27,249
I see nothing.

537
00:37:27,316 --> 00:37:28,384
It starts from here.

538
00:37:29,418 --> 00:37:31,320
The audio from this section.

539
00:37:31,387 --> 00:37:33,289
I had the forensics lab analyze it.

540
00:37:38,194 --> 00:37:39,895
<i>…from the rooftop…</i>

541
00:37:40,763 --> 00:37:42,231
<i>…Uno…</i>

542
00:37:48,838 --> 00:37:50,740
<i>Push him off the rooftop.</i>

543
00:37:51,273 --> 00:37:54,210
<i>Kill Uno and make it look like a suicide.</i>

544
00:38:05,154 --> 00:38:06,689
Well, see you again.

545
00:38:06,756 --> 00:38:08,124
I already told you.

546
00:38:08,190 --> 00:38:09,358
We won't be meeting again.

547
00:38:09,425 --> 00:38:11,193
Is that so?

548
00:38:11,260 --> 00:38:14,029
I am quite certain
you will come to see me, though.

549
00:38:16,499 --> 00:38:17,733
I'll take over.

550
00:38:18,334 --> 00:38:19,368
This way.

551
00:38:48,431 --> 00:38:50,132
You here for a consultation too?

552
00:38:55,838 --> 00:38:57,139
I'm sorry.

553
00:38:58,340 --> 00:39:00,075
That won't be possible today.

554
00:39:05,548 --> 00:39:06,816
Kenshin…

555
00:39:13,322 --> 00:39:14,857
You should stay out of this.

556
00:41:01,330 --> 00:41:03,532
<i>Narita's son has turned himself in.</i>

557
00:41:04,333 --> 00:41:06,001
<i>Is he actually talking this time?</i>

558
00:41:06,769 --> 00:41:08,370
<i>He's incredibly cooperative.</i>

559
00:41:10,873 --> 00:41:12,308
How is Makoto?

560
00:41:12,374 --> 00:41:14,777
He's completely back to his usual self.

561
00:41:15,544 --> 00:41:17,713
Well, that is troublesome too.

562
00:41:20,683 --> 00:41:22,785
You said something before.

563
00:41:22,851 --> 00:41:23,886
What?

564
00:41:24,386 --> 00:41:26,555
That you and Mr. Tagusari go way back.

565
00:41:28,090 --> 00:41:29,758
We're from the same hometown.

566
00:41:31,160 --> 00:41:32,761
Are you connected by those murders?

567
00:41:34,863 --> 00:41:35,864
What?

568
00:41:36,966 --> 00:41:38,934
April 26, 1995.

569
00:41:39,001 --> 00:41:42,771
The Yomogida-cho family murder case.

570
00:41:46,108 --> 00:41:49,111
The culprit still hasn't been caught.

571
00:41:52,314 --> 00:41:53,949
The statute has expired, you know.

572
00:41:59,321 --> 00:42:00,889
What about the evidence?

573
00:42:01,724 --> 00:42:02,758
Did you find it?

574
00:42:05,260 --> 00:42:06,895
I made sure to search thoroughly.

575
00:42:07,396 --> 00:42:10,232
I'll run to the supermarket.
Keep working on that.

576
00:42:24,947 --> 00:42:27,683
But there was nothing there.

577
00:42:33,422 --> 00:42:34,390
Really?

578
00:42:36,458 --> 00:42:37,459
Yes.

579
00:42:38,227 --> 00:42:41,563
So, you don't need to worry all that much.

580
00:42:41,630 --> 00:42:43,032
You really want…

581
00:42:44,900 --> 00:42:47,169
to protect those brothers, huh?

582
00:43:06,288 --> 00:43:07,923
<i>Now we have Tsuda's notebook</i>…

583
00:43:07,990 --> 00:43:11,160
<i>We should be able to find out</i>
<i>what happened 30 years ago.</i>

584
00:43:12,127 --> 00:43:15,631
"However, the darkness surrounding
the illicit manufacturing runs deep.

585
00:43:16,165 --> 00:43:17,299
The involved parties

586
00:43:17,966 --> 00:43:21,236
include the Karashima Metal Factory,
the Igarashi-gumi,

587
00:43:22,171 --> 00:43:23,439
and beyond that…"

588
00:43:25,908 --> 00:43:27,776
Who could it be at a time like this?

589
00:43:36,251 --> 00:43:37,386
Why?

590
00:43:51,834 --> 00:43:52,968
<i>You don't think…</i>

591
00:43:53,035 --> 00:43:54,503
<i>Mr. Koike was involved too?</i>

592
00:43:54,570 --> 00:43:56,705
Everyone will continue to be happy.

593
00:43:56,772 --> 00:43:58,774
Do you trust Tsuda more?!

594
00:43:58,841 --> 00:44:01,076
<i>Do you want to know the truth that badly?</i>

595
00:44:01,844 --> 00:44:02,811
Subtitle translation by: Nix S.

